article.description: Ivan Gandia-Rosa registered 17 points as North Florida edged past Southern Miss 66-63 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Gandia-Rosa lifts North Florida past Southern Miss 66-63
article.linkText: Gandia-Rosa lifts North Florida past Southern Miss 66-63
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Ivan Gandia-Rosa registered 17 points as North Florida edged past Southern Miss 66-63 on Thursday night. Southern Miss pulled to 62-61 with 16 seconds left on Leonard Harper-Baker's layup, but Emmanuel Adedoyin and Gandia-Rosa each made a pair of free throws to seal it for the Ospreys. Carter Hendricksen had 15 points for North Florida (3-1). Adedoyin finished with 12 points. Tyler Stevenson had 13 points for the Golden Eagles (1-2). Artur Konontsuk added 13 points. Gabe Watson had 12 points. North Florida faces Trinity Baptist at home on Monday. Southern Miss plays Iowa State on the road on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
